dct_description_sm: United States. Geological Survey. U.S.G.S. Alternate title: Providence. Relief shown by 20 feet contour interval and spot heights. Surveyed in 1885 and 1887. Surveyed in cooperation with the states of Massachusetts and Rhode Island. Triangulation, coast line and part of coast by the U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey. Verso: Description of the topographic map of the United States.
